## Steps for Execution

Follow the below steps to run the **Cab Booking Application** successfully on your local system.

---

## 1. Clone the Repository

Clone the project repository from GitHub:

```bash id="4h5h8c"
git clone <repository-url>
```

Navigate into the project folder:

```bash id="xq8d2n"
cd Cab-Booking-Application
```

---

# Backend Execution

## 2. Navigate to the Server Folder

Open the terminal and move to the backend directory:

```bash id="3wqz3h"
cd server
```

---

## 3. Install Backend Dependencies

Install all required Node.js packages:

```bash id="8jzv5w"
npm install
```

---

## 4. Configure Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file inside the **server** folder and add the required configuration:

```env id="9s8m1d"
PORT=5000

MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string

JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

Replace the values with your MongoDB connection URL and secret key.

---

## 5. Start the Backend Server

Run the backend server using:

```bash id="1j8k2v"
npm run dev
```

If the server starts successfully, you will see:

```text id="2t3v9b"
Server is running on port 5000
MongoDB Connected Successfully
```

The backend API will now be available at:

```text id="n8q5z1"
http://localhost:5000
```

---

# Frontend Execution

## 6. Navigate to the Client Folder

Open another terminal window and move to the frontend directory:

```bash id="4y8s2p"
cd client
```

---

## 7. Install Frontend Dependencies

Install all React application packages:

```bash id="6w3k9p"
npm install
```

---

## 8. Start the React Development Server

Run the frontend application:

```bash id="7k2m4v"
npm run dev
```

The Vite development server will start and display:

```text id="9f5r8x"
VITE ready in XXX ms

Local: http://localhost:5173/
```

Open the URL in your browser:

```text id="c3x7m1"
http://localhost:5173/
```

---

